1
00:01:41,666 --> 00:01:43,250
[KONDO]
My name is Yukio Kondo.

2
00:01:43,333 --> 00:01:44,791
Just a regular teenager.

3
00:01:44,875 --> 00:01:47,291
Average in grades,
average in sports.

4
00:01:47,375 --> 00:01:49,166
Got a couple of friends
and no enemies.

5
00:01:49,250 --> 00:01:52,791
I don't need to be popular
and I don't need to stand out.

6
00:01:55,250 --> 00:01:55,791
[KONDO]
Good morning.

7
00:01:55,875 --> 00:01:57,125
Uh, yeah.

8
00:01:57,208 --> 00:01:58,750
Thanks. You, too.

9
00:01:58,833 --> 00:01:59,541
Gotta go!

10
00:01:59,625 --> 00:02:00,583
[KONDO]
Huh?

11
00:02:00,666 --> 00:02:03,416
Jeez, not very
friendly today, huh?

12
00:02:07,375 --> 00:02:09,833
[KONDO]
Was it something I said?

13
00:02:09,916 --> 00:02:10,541
Oh, hey.

14
00:02:10,625 --> 00:02:12,333
Good morning, Yuki.

15
00:02:12,416 --> 00:02:14,583
What's up? You look extra dull.

16
00:02:14,666 --> 00:02:16,291
This is how I always look.

17
00:02:16,375 --> 00:02:18,041
[TSUTSUI] You should
take a cue from Handa.

18
00:02:18,125 --> 00:02:19,416
The guy's got style.

19
00:02:19,500 --> 00:02:21,708
[AIZAWA] Not to mention
that sharp look in his eye.

20
00:02:21,791 --> 00:02:22,416
Uh?

21
00:02:22,500 --> 00:02:25,416
[STUDENTS whispering]

22
00:02:25,500 --> 00:02:26,833
What's the matter now?

23
00:02:26,916 --> 00:02:28,375
I think I'm being watched.

24
00:02:28,458 --> 00:02:31,166
Ha, ha! Yeah, right! As if.

25
00:02:31,250 --> 00:02:33,583
[KONDO]
It could happen!

26
00:02:33,666 --> 00:02:36,208
[KONDO] I don't care what
he says. Something is up.

27
00:02:36,291 --> 00:02:37,791
Why so glum, Yukicchi?

28
00:02:37,875 --> 00:02:40,500
I'm not. We just can't all
be as chipper as you, Reo.

29
00:02:40,583 --> 00:02:42,500
Oh, come on, you can tell me.

30
00:02:42,583 --> 00:02:44,916
It's obvious something's
bothering you.

31
00:02:45,000 --> 00:02:47,041
How about this? After school,

32
00:02:47,125 --> 00:02:49,375
we'll go to the Handa Force
headquarters, and we'll talk.

33
00:02:49,458 --> 00:02:52,125
Do you promise not to make
fun of me if I tell you?

34
00:02:52,208 --> 00:02:54,166
[REO]
I would never!

35
00:02:54,250 --> 00:02:55,833
Not even if the
thing bugging you

36
00:02:55,916 --> 00:02:57,250
was that nothing
was bugging you!

37
00:02:57,333 --> 00:02:58,750
[KONDO] You're making
fun of me right now.

38
00:02:58,833 --> 00:03:00,208
[REO]
Maybe a little.

39
00:03:00,291 --> 00:03:01,416
[KONDO]
Should've known.

40
00:03:01,500 --> 00:03:03,000
Reo doesn't have a
care in the world.

41
00:03:03,083 --> 00:03:05,333
I can't expect him to
relate to my problems.

42
00:03:05,416 --> 00:03:09,583
But I'd be the same way if girls
fawned over me like they do him.

43
00:03:14,125 --> 00:03:17,375
[KONDO gasping]

44
00:03:17,458 --> 00:03:19,416
[KONDO]
Uh! Holy crap!

45
00:03:19,500 --> 00:03:23,375
Someone gave me a note sealed
with a heart-shaped sticker!

46
00:03:25,083 --> 00:03:26,458
Morning.

47
00:03:26,541 --> 00:03:28,541
I hope you're all ready for
an exciting biology class.

48
00:03:28,625 --> 00:03:30,416
[KONDO]
That can only mean one thing.

49
00:03:30,500 --> 00:03:33,083
It's a love letter!

50
00:03:33,166 --> 00:03:34,416
But that's crazy...

51
00:03:34,500 --> 00:03:38,000
I've barely spoken to any
girls at all this year!

52
00:03:38,083 --> 00:03:41,958
Well, either way,
this is awesome!

53
00:03:42,041 --> 00:03:46,125
Except I have no idea what I'm
supposed to do with this thing.

54
00:03:46,208 --> 00:03:48,208
I guess I could ask Reo.

55
00:03:48,291 --> 00:03:49,250
No, wait!

56
00:03:49,333 --> 00:03:50,500
Showing this note to everyone

57
00:03:50,583 --> 00:03:52,583
would be rude to the girl
who gave it to me.

58
00:03:52,666 --> 00:03:54,666
Besides, how do I know
it's a love letter?

59
00:03:54,750 --> 00:03:57,833
It's not like I've ever
gotten one before.

60
00:03:57,916 --> 00:04:00,458
But I mean, with a
sticker like that,

61
00:04:00,541 --> 00:04:02,333
what else could it be?

62
00:04:02,416 --> 00:04:05,583
What are you planning on using
your pressed flower for, Kondo?

63
00:04:05,666 --> 00:04:07,875
A postcard? A bookmark?

64
00:04:07,958 --> 00:04:10,166
Maybe... harassment?

65
00:04:10,250 --> 00:04:10,791
[OKAYAMA]
Whoa!

66
00:04:10,875 --> 00:04:11,500
[gasps]

67
00:04:11,583 --> 00:04:12,875
Well that's a new one.

68
00:04:12,958 --> 00:04:15,291
"Harassing people
with pressed flowers."

69
00:04:15,375 --> 00:04:17,833
To each his own! [laughs]

70
00:04:17,916 --> 00:04:20,208
That's not what I meant.
You don't understand!

71
00:04:20,291 --> 00:04:22,458
Way to go, Yukicchi!

72
00:04:22,541 --> 00:04:23,708
[KONDO]
This sucks.

73
00:04:23,791 --> 00:04:25,166
Even if they are harassing me,

74
00:04:25,250 --> 00:04:28,333
I still don't know how I'm
supposed to deal with this.

75
00:04:30,250 --> 00:04:32,958
I see. A love letter, huh?

76
00:04:33,041 --> 00:04:34,250
Yeah, I was hoping you could

77
00:04:34,333 --> 00:04:36,541
help me take a look
at this objectively.

78
00:04:36,625 --> 00:04:37,791
You came to the right man.

79
00:04:37,875 --> 00:04:39,291
Huh?

80
00:04:39,375 --> 00:04:41,583
'Cause I know from experience
that this is a challenge!

81
00:04:41,666 --> 00:04:45,166
It is? Then why is there a
sticker shaped like a heart?

82
00:04:45,250 --> 00:04:46,750
To mislead you.

83
00:04:46,833 --> 00:04:48,166
[TSUTSUI laughs]

84
00:04:48,250 --> 00:04:50,416
[TSUTSUI] This very thing
happened to me last year.

85
00:04:50,500 --> 00:04:52,625
They came out of nowhere,
ripped off my clothes,

86
00:04:52,708 --> 00:04:53,875
and forced me to--

87
00:04:53,958 --> 00:04:56,500
That's enough, Tsutsui!
Not another single word!

88
00:04:56,583 --> 00:04:58,750
The girl that sent this
to you is Yoriko Maki,

89
00:04:58,833 --> 00:05:00,541
who most people would
call a five-out-of-ten

90
00:05:00,625 --> 00:05:01,625
on the beauty scale.

91
00:05:01,708 --> 00:05:02,791
Wait, you mean you know her?

92
00:05:02,875 --> 00:05:05,708
I never did find out
what that was about.

93
00:05:05,791 --> 00:05:08,166
[AIZAWA] She's plain and
average in every category.

94
00:05:08,250 --> 00:05:10,541
Which, no offense, makes
you perfect for each other,

95
00:05:10,625 --> 00:05:12,500
so it has to be a love letter.

96
00:05:12,583 --> 00:05:14,458
Phew. That's a relief to hear.

97
00:05:14,541 --> 00:05:17,291
But honestly, I don't have
any idea who this girl is.

98
00:05:17,375 --> 00:05:19,458
Well, she doesn't really
stand out much.

99
00:05:19,541 --> 00:05:20,750
What's this now?

100
00:05:20,833 --> 00:05:22,791
Spring's finally come
to our late bloomer?

101
00:05:22,875 --> 00:05:24,500
Oh, crap, you were listening?

102
00:05:24,583 --> 00:05:27,875
This is a big day for the Handa
Force, and deserves celebration!

103
00:05:27,958 --> 00:05:29,166
We should have a party
at headquarters

104
00:05:29,250 --> 00:05:30,291
tonight after school!

105
00:05:30,375 --> 00:05:31,541
[KONDO]
Will you cut it out?

106
00:05:31,625 --> 00:05:33,333
It's not like anything's
happened yet.

107
00:05:33,416 --> 00:05:34,875
[TSUTSUI]
You ask me,

108
00:05:34,958 --> 00:05:36,708
I don't think romance should
be allowed in the Handa Force.

109
00:05:36,791 --> 00:05:39,500
[REO] Huh?! But I have,
like, 300 girlfriends!

110
00:05:39,583 --> 00:05:41,875
--[TSUTSUI] Liar!
--[REO] It's true!

111
00:05:41,958 --> 00:05:44,000
[TSUTSUI] But the idea
that she's plain and average

112
00:05:44,083 --> 00:05:45,041
is just so--

113
00:05:45,125 --> 00:05:46,250
[REO]
So Yukicchi?

114
00:05:46,333 --> 00:05:48,375
[KONDO] Hey! What's
the problem with that?

115
00:05:48,458 --> 00:05:52,000
[TSUTSUI, REO chuckle]

116
00:05:52,083 --> 00:05:53,250
[HANDA]
I never would have guessed

117
00:05:53,333 --> 00:05:55,708
that pressing flowers
was so much fun.

118
00:05:55,791 --> 00:05:57,041
[REO]
You should comb your hair.

119
00:05:57,125 --> 00:05:58,958
That way you'll look your
best for her confession.

120
00:05:59,041 --> 00:06:03,083
And we should come up with
a romantic response, as well.

121
00:06:03,166 --> 00:06:06,291
Why not use the pressed flower
we made in class as a card?

122
00:06:06,375 --> 00:06:08,916
You can write how you feel on it
and give it to her at the gym.

123
00:06:09,000 --> 00:06:11,291
That's... a little out
of character for me.

124
00:06:11,375 --> 00:06:15,666
All right, guys, don't worry,
I've got you covered.

125
00:06:15,750 --> 00:06:17,458
[KONDO]
Not literally those words!

126
00:06:17,541 --> 00:06:18,625
Tsu-Tsu!

127
00:06:18,708 --> 00:06:20,833
Well, it's at least
better than nothing.

128
00:06:20,916 --> 00:06:21,666
Right?

129
00:06:21,750 --> 00:06:22,666
[gasps]

130
00:06:22,750 --> 00:06:26,208
[STUDENTS whispering]

131
00:06:26,291 --> 00:06:27,875
[KONDO]
Of course!

132
00:06:27,958 --> 00:06:30,708
This is why everyone's been
acting so weird around me!

133
00:06:30,791 --> 00:06:33,333
Even if I'm boring, being
part of the Handa force

134
00:06:33,416 --> 00:06:35,625
has made me popular
by association.

135
00:06:35,708 --> 00:06:37,041
And regardless of who sent it,

136
00:06:37,125 --> 00:06:40,125
I got a love letter from
a girl! That's huge!

137
00:06:40,208 --> 00:06:42,208
So the reason everyone's
talking about me

138
00:06:42,291 --> 00:06:44,208
is 'cause they're jealous!

139
00:06:44,291 --> 00:06:48,083
Well take a good, hard look,
because I'm transforming.

140
00:06:48,166 --> 00:06:51,416
Thanks to Handa, this
duckling has become a swan!

141
00:06:51,500 --> 00:06:53,250
[HANDA laughs]

142
00:06:55,208 --> 00:06:57,458
You're too average to be a
member of the Handa Force,

143
00:06:57,541 --> 00:06:59,583
so you should just quit.

144
00:07:01,583 --> 00:07:03,083
That's all I really
wanted to say.

145
00:07:03,166 --> 00:07:06,750
[YORIKO'S FRIEND] So Yori,
are we done here or what?

146
00:07:06,833 --> 00:07:08,541
[REO]
Oh, snap.

147
00:07:08,625 --> 00:07:11,583
[AIZAWA] Man, the poor guy
never even stood a chance.

148
00:07:11,666 --> 00:07:15,208
[TSUTSUI] She used that heart
shape to toy with his emotions!

149
00:07:15,291 --> 00:07:17,666
[REO] Hey, don't let
this get you down!

150
00:07:17,750 --> 00:07:19,125
Yeah, forget what she said.

151
00:07:19,208 --> 00:07:20,416
You're a member of
the Handa Force,

152
00:07:20,500 --> 00:07:22,958
and we'll always have your back!

153
00:07:23,875 --> 00:07:25,583
That kinda blew.

154
00:07:25,666 --> 00:07:27,250
Yukicchi?

155
00:07:27,333 --> 00:07:29,500
Honestly, I should have
known this would happen.

156
00:07:29,583 --> 00:07:31,500
I'm just an average nobody.

157
00:07:31,583 --> 00:07:34,083
Guys like me don't get love
confessions behind the gym,

158
00:07:34,166 --> 00:07:36,666
you know? It's just
a sad fact of life.

159
00:07:36,750 --> 00:07:38,958
[laughs]

160
00:07:39,041 --> 00:07:40,250
You okay?

161
00:07:40,333 --> 00:07:45,791
Yeah, totally fine.
Don't worry. 100%-- okay!

162
00:07:45,875 --> 00:07:47,083
[ALL gasp]

163
00:07:47,166 --> 00:07:47,916
[AIZAWA]
Yuki?!

164
00:07:48,000 --> 00:07:49,625
[REO]
He's so not okay!

165
00:07:49,708 --> 00:07:52,208
[TSUTSUI]
Wait, come back!

166
00:07:54,583 --> 00:07:57,208
[KONDO] I've spent my whole life
being nothing but average,

167
00:07:57,291 --> 00:07:59,583
so why did I get
so carried away?

168
00:07:59,666 --> 00:08:02,416
Once a duckling, always
a duckling, right?

169
00:08:02,500 --> 00:08:03,958
For a second,

170
00:08:04,041 --> 00:08:06,375
I actually believed someone
thought I was cool like Handa.

171
00:08:06,458 --> 00:08:08,041
I'm so stupid.

172
00:08:08,125 --> 00:08:08,750
[BOTH gasp]

173
00:08:08,833 --> 00:08:10,208
S-Sorry about that.

174
00:08:10,291 --> 00:08:11,791
Yeah. Me, too.

175
00:08:11,875 --> 00:08:12,958
[KONDO]
Oh, it's you.

176
00:08:13,041 --> 00:08:15,958
Uh! Wait, I know you!

177
00:08:18,250 --> 00:08:21,875
[inaudible]

178
00:08:24,375 --> 00:08:26,041
You attacked me in Kyoto.

179
00:08:26,125 --> 00:08:27,541
[chuckles nervously]

180
00:08:27,625 --> 00:08:29,916
So, uh, what are you
doing out here, anyway?

181
00:08:30,000 --> 00:08:31,458
Are all those flowers for class?

182
00:08:31,541 --> 00:08:32,916
No, of course not!

183
00:08:33,000 --> 00:08:35,416
Don't go jumping to
conclusions, okay?

184
00:08:35,500 --> 00:08:37,708
They're, uh... Well...

185
00:08:37,791 --> 00:08:40,916
I'm gonna use them
to harass people!

186
00:08:41,000 --> 00:08:44,000
[KONDO] He does realize I
didn't mean that, doesn't he?

187
00:08:44,083 --> 00:08:47,458
On that note, why does he always
say things he doesn't mean?

188
00:08:47,541 --> 00:08:49,333
All right then, good
luck with all that.

189
00:08:49,416 --> 00:08:52,250
I don't need luck! Harassing
people's easy for me!

190
00:08:52,333 --> 00:08:54,125
[HANDA groans]

191
00:08:54,208 --> 00:08:55,708
[KONDO]
Handa goes through so much

192
00:08:55,791 --> 00:08:57,916
trying to live up to what
people think of him.

193
00:08:58,000 --> 00:09:01,875
But he's really just a shy
guy with a kind heart.

194
00:09:01,958 --> 00:09:05,416
That's probably why he's
swayed by others so easily.

195
00:09:05,500 --> 00:09:07,458
Same as me.

196
00:09:09,166 --> 00:09:11,208
Handa. Take this.

197
00:09:11,291 --> 00:09:14,500
[HANDA]
Uh?

198
00:09:14,583 --> 00:09:16,291
Well, I'll see you in class.

199
00:09:16,375 --> 00:09:17,458
[HANDA]
Uh. Hold on.

200
00:09:17,541 --> 00:09:19,333
[KONDO]
Huh?

201
00:09:19,416 --> 00:09:23,958
Thank you. I... guess.

202
00:09:24,041 --> 00:09:26,708
No thanks necessary.

203
00:09:28,000 --> 00:09:30,666
[KONDO] I think I belong in
the Handa Force after all.

204
00:09:30,750 --> 00:09:31,333
[REO]
Yukicchi!

205
00:09:31,416 --> 00:09:32,750
Huh?

206
00:09:32,833 --> 00:09:34,333
[AIZAWA] What are you doing
running off by yourself?

207
00:09:34,416 --> 00:09:35,833
[KONDO]
Ha, ha. You guys.

208
00:09:35,916 --> 00:09:37,333
[AIZAWA laughing]

209
00:09:37,416 --> 00:09:38,416
[KONDO]
I'm good.

210
00:09:38,500 --> 00:09:40,125
[TSUTSUI]
Don't scare us like that.

211
00:09:40,208 --> 00:09:42,250
As long as you're okay.

212
00:09:42,333 --> 00:09:43,541
[KONDO]
I don't know how I ended up

213
00:09:43,625 --> 00:09:45,125
joining them in the first place.

214
00:09:45,208 --> 00:09:46,833
But I'm sure Handa had
something to do with it.

215
00:09:46,916 --> 00:09:48,041
[HANDA humming]

216
00:09:48,125 --> 00:09:50,291
[KONDO] He just has
that effect on people.

217
00:09:50,375 --> 00:09:52,625
[HANDA]
That was so nice of him.

218
00:09:56,166 --> 00:10:00,708
[HANDA] Ah! He really does
harass people with flowers!

219
00:10:00,791 --> 00:10:04,625
[KAWAFUJI] And so their
relationship got even worse.

220
00:10:05,083 --> 00:10:07,166
[NEO] We are the
<i>Bishoujo</i> Pictures Club!

221
00:10:07,250 --> 00:10:08,875
What is a <i>bishoujo</i> ? you ask?

222
00:10:08,958 --> 00:10:11,083
Some may say it's
simply a "cute girl,"

223
00:10:11,166 --> 00:10:12,583
but those people are casuals!

224
00:10:12,666 --> 00:10:14,250
Filthy plebs!

225
00:10:14,333 --> 00:10:16,666
In order to better explore
the concept of " <i>Bishoujo</i> ,"

226
00:10:16,750 --> 00:10:18,208
we release a periodic bulletin,

227
00:10:18,291 --> 00:10:21,125
filled with manga and
charming illustrations.

228
00:10:21,208 --> 00:10:22,833
Hmm...

229
00:10:22,916 --> 00:10:24,708
[TAKOYAKI]
Let's see!

230
00:10:26,291 --> 00:10:28,000
[NEO] Despite having
only three members,

231
00:10:28,083 --> 00:10:31,208
we're quite satisfied with our
club activities. However...

232
00:10:31,291 --> 00:10:33,333
The Student Council has
decided to terminate

233
00:10:33,416 --> 00:10:35,416
your cute girl club
as of this term.

234
00:10:35,500 --> 00:10:37,708
[NEO]
...we are in a serious bind now.

235
00:10:37,791 --> 00:10:39,208
No, you can't!

236
00:10:39,291 --> 00:10:41,333
We are not just cogs
in the imperial machine

237
00:10:41,416 --> 00:10:42,791
that can be taken out!

238
00:10:42,875 --> 00:10:44,958
My heart aches in pain!

239
00:10:45,041 --> 00:10:47,500
No, no, no, no, no,
no, no, no, no!

240
00:10:47,583 --> 00:10:50,375
Why is the Empire taking its
base frustrations out on us?!

241
00:10:50,458 --> 00:10:52,375
Because, there's no
reason the school

242
00:10:52,458 --> 00:10:55,250
should be spending its precious
funds on three students' hobby.

243
00:10:55,333 --> 00:10:56,500
Understand?

244
00:10:56,583 --> 00:10:57,791
Damn your eyes!

245
00:10:57,875 --> 00:11:00,166
Your words don't scare us,
Student Council dog!

246
00:11:00,250 --> 00:11:01,583
Look, you guys
are more than free

247
00:11:01,666 --> 00:11:03,916
