slice-of-life comedy!

287
00:12:30,041 --> 00:12:32,708
We'll just make up some story.

288
00:12:35,500 --> 00:12:36,833
Let's do it.

289
00:12:36,916 --> 00:12:40,041
[NEO] That was all the
convincing we needed.

290
00:12:40,125 --> 00:12:42,875
Do we have any idea what
kind of character Handa is?

291
00:12:42,958 --> 00:12:45,875
[TAKOYAKI] No clue. We stay
away from the popular crowd,

292
00:12:45,958 --> 00:12:47,750
so we never really see him.

293
00:12:47,833 --> 00:12:53,500
He's always by himself, so maybe
she should be a cool loner.

294
00:12:53,583 --> 00:12:55,666
No. I've heard he's
compassionate,

295
00:12:55,750 --> 00:12:59,333
so she'd be better as
an older sister figure.

296
00:13:01,250 --> 00:13:03,250
Or a spunky tomboy
with a cool catchphrase.

297
00:13:03,333 --> 00:13:04,791
[HANDA-CHAN]
Believe it.

298
00:13:04,875 --> 00:13:10,291
[ALL groaning]

299
00:13:10,375 --> 00:13:11,875
Okay, new plan: we split up

300
00:13:11,958 --> 00:13:14,375
and make character profiles
based on our own tastes.

301
00:13:14,458 --> 00:13:15,958
Yeah, good idea.

302
00:13:16,041 --> 00:13:18,416
I mean, the character doesn't
have to be exactly like Handa.

303
00:13:18,500 --> 00:13:19,583
Then we'll meet back up

304
00:13:19,666 --> 00:13:21,375
once we've each finished
our first drafts.

305
00:13:21,458 --> 00:13:23,708
Whichever manga is the
best is the one we sell.

306
00:13:23,791 --> 00:13:25,375
May the best Handa- <i>chan</i> win!

307
00:13:25,458 --> 00:13:26,750
Good luck, you guys!

308
00:13:26,833 --> 00:13:28,791
Yeah!

309
00:13:28,875 --> 00:13:30,500
[NEO] The only problem
with this new plan

310
00:13:30,583 --> 00:13:32,458
